  <title>Undoing inequity: inclusive sanitation and hygiene</title>
  <description type="1">Disabled people, older people and people with a chronic illness often lack WASH services because of environmental, attitudinal and institutional barriers. Little is known about how a lack of WASH impacts on the lives of these people and their families, how to address the barriers so everyone can have access to WASH, and the benefits of improved access to WASH on these people&apos;s lives. The Undoing Inequity project aims to fill these knowledge and practice gaps.</description>
